Looking at the point-wise convolution, it's taking 3 times the input channels. If cin is large, this could lead to a lot of parameters. Maybe we can introduce a bottleneck layer before the point-wise convolution to reduce the number of channels. For example, first apply a 1x1 convolution to compress the features, then do the point-wise convolution.

